# INTERNAL WORKFLOW

Follow this process internally:

Step 1. Generate up to 10 candidate facets from the input alone.
Use only evidence from USER_INTENTION, URL, and RAW_METADATA.

Step 2. Compare those 10 candidates against FACETS_FROM_DB.
If an existing database facet matches the same concept well, reuse the database facet spelling exactly.

Step 3. Re-rank all candidates by relevance and evidence strength.

Step 4. Keep only the best candidates.
Maximum total facets across all groups: 5.

Step 5. Place each selected facet into the most appropriate group:
- facet_format
- facet_topic
- facet_function
- facet_tech_stack

---

# FACET GROUP DEFINITIONS

facet_format
The type of resource itself.
This describes what the resource is.

facet_topic
What the resource is about.
This describes the subject, domain, or concept.

facet_function
What the resource is used for.
This describes the practical purpose or capability.

facet_tech_stack
Named technologies actually used by the resource itself.

---

# SELECTION RULES

Prefer facets that are:
- explicitly supported
- specific
- reusable
- high-signal

Avoid facets that are:
- vague
- generic
- speculative
- marketing-style
- not grounded in the input

Discard low-signal facets such as:
software, project, tool, app, useful, system

Do not include hosting websites as tech_stack unless the input clearly shows they are part of the resource technology itself.

---

# NORMALIZATION RULES

When creating a NEW facet:
- prefer a short canonical form
- lowercase by default
- use a single word when possible
- avoid punctuation
- avoid decorative wording

If FACETS_FROM_DB already contains a matching concept, reuse that value exactly instead of inventing a variant.

Remove duplicates.

---

# LIMITS

- Up to 2 values in facet_format
- Up to 3 values in facet_topic
- Up to 2 values in facet_function
- Up to 2 values in facet_tech_stack
- Maximum total facets across all groups: 5

Return empty arrays where nothing is strongly supported.

